# MilePilot Design Bible (required for UI work)

Before creating or materially changing any **screen, modal, card, or user-facing copy**, read and apply:

**`docs/MILEPILOT-DESIGN-BIBLE.md`**

## Quick gates

1. **3-second test** — user knows what this is and what to do
2. **One primary action** — no competing CTAs
3. **Benefit-first, minimal copy** — no GPS jargon, no bullet clutter
4. **Reuse existing components** — `.brand-bar`, `.card`, `.mode-card`, `.premium-btn`, tokens from `docs/brand/tokens.css`
5. **AutoPilot** naming and blue pulse conventions
6. **Do not redesign locked screens** — see `docs/ONBOARDING_V1_LOCK.md`, `docs/DESIGN_LOCKED.md`

## Philosophy

> If it doesn't make the decision easier, it probably doesn't need to be there.

## Frozen screens

`#knowYou` (MP-002) and other locked onboarding — **bug fixes only** unless user explicitly approves redesign.
